race.comment: Open race. SOUTHERN AURORAS (5) is a progressive mare in good form. Placed last time in what has turned out to be a hot form race behind Billie The Great. Drawn for a soft run and expected to go close. GEEGEE STRAWBERRY (7) is ready to win after two runs back. Hit the line strongly over 1200m at this track, beaten 2.5 lengths into fifth. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. GEEGEES LEGACY (4) returned to winning form as favourite over 1200m at Launceston nine days ago, getting home by 0.8 lengths. Steps up a level but expected to gibe a sight despite the tricky gate. SWINGING IT (9) has a moderate winning strike-rate but did a good job when returning from a break last time at this track, finishing second and only 2 lengths from the winner at the end of 1100m. Likely improver with top-three prospects. LADY FERN (11) wasn't far away behind Billie The Great latest and gets chance to atone.
